# Connecting to Microsoft 365 with PowerShell

This guide walks you through the steps to connect to Microsoft 365 using PowerShell. You'll need to install the necessary modules and authenticate your session to manage Microsoft 365 services.

## Prerequisites

- PowerShell 5.1 or higher
- Microsoft 365 admin credentials
- Install required modules

## Step 1: Install the Microsoft 365 PowerShell Module

Before connecting, you need to install the required PowerShell module for Microsoft 365. Open PowerShell as an administrator and run the following command:

```powershell
Install-Module -Name Microsoft.Online.SharePoint.PowerShell -Force -AllowClobber
Install-Module -Name MSOnline -Force
Step 2: Import the Module
After installation, import the module into your PowerShell session:

powershell
Copy
Edit
Import-Module MSOnline
Step 3: Connect to Microsoft 365
Use the following command to connect to your Microsoft 365 tenant:

powershell
Copy
Edit
Connect-MsolService
You will be prompted to enter your admin credentials.

Step 4: Verify the Connection
Once connected, verify the connection by running:

powershell
Copy
Edit
Get-MsolCompanyInformation
If the connection is successful, it will return information about your Microsoft 365 tenant.

This guide helps you quickly set up and start managing your Microsoft 365 environment via PowerShell. For more advanced management tasks, explore additional PowerShell cmdlets and modules.
